execute

public Result<?> execute()
Description copied from interface: Task
This method models the the Divide and conquer algorithm. (1) if(getStatus() == Task.Status.DECOMPOSE) Any subclass implementing this method should divide the existing task into smaller subtasks, pack the subtasks in a Result object and return them. The returned subtasks are consumed by a Space object by queueing them again for execution on different machine in the cluster. If the base case of recursion has been reached during the process of decomposition, then the value can be returned in the Result object, instead of subtasks. (2) if(getStatus() == Task.Status.COMPOSE) This method should compose results of smaller subtasks that were earlier generated by this task during the 'Divide' phase, into a single value that can be consumed by the parent of this task in the overall recursion tree. See Task.putValues(List) and Task.getValues() to know how values can be passed to setup the 'Conquer' phase of execution.

Specified by:
execute in interface Task<java.util.List<TspTask.City>>
Returns:
A Result object containing either subtasks that have been created during this decomposition stage, or value of a base case in the underlying recursion, or value obtained by composing results of smaller subtasks that were generated by this task in the 'Divide' phase
